Garlic Parmesan Shrimp Rice Bowls üç§
Ingredients:
For the Shrimp:
1 pound large shrimp, peeled and deveined
1 tablespoon olive oil
1 teaspoon garlic powder
1/2 teaspoon onion powder
1/4 teaspoon salt
1/8 teaspoon black pepper
For the Rice:
1 cup cooked rice
For the Garlic Parmesan Sauce:
1/4 cup mayonnaise
2 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese
1 clove garlic, minced
1 tablespoon lemon juice
1/4 teaspoon salt
1/8 teaspoon black pepper
Instructions:
Grill the Shrimp: Preheat grill to medium-high heat. Season the shrimp with garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper. Grill the shrimp for 2-3 minutes per side, or until cooked through.
Make the Garlic Parmesan Sauce: In a small bowl, whisk together mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, garlic, lemon juice, salt, and pepper.
Assemble the Bowls: Divide the cooked rice among bowls. Top with grilled shrimp and drizzle generously with the Garlic Parmesan Sauce.
Tips:
You can use any type of shrimp you like for this recipe.
For a spicier sauce, add a pinch of red pepper flakes to the Garlic Parmesan Sauce.
Serve the bowls with your favorite side dishes, such as a green salad or a side of steamed vegetables.
